<title>Section Summary</title>
<list id="fs-id1167067105259"><item>Compton scattering provided evidence that photon-electron interactions abide by the principles of conservation of momentum and conservation of energy.</item>
<item>The momentum of individual photons, quantified by  <m:math> <m:mrow> <m:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:mstyle><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac> <m:mi>h</m:mi> <m:mi>λ</m:mi> </m:mfrac> </m:mrow></m:math>, can be used to explain observations of comets and may lead to future space technologies.</item>
<item>Electromagnetic waves and matter have both wave-like and particle-like properties. This phenomenon is defined as particle-wave duality.</item>
</list></section>

